The paper deals with the problem of fine-grained image retrieval, which involves the use of computer vision techniques to identify and retrieve images that belong to a specific category or sub-category. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning approach to simultaneously localize discriminative regions and generate efficient binary codes, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as neural networks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of image retrieval techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
